reviewText: WrestleMaina is the biggest WWE PPV of the year. The problem with PPVs of late is they seem to be all thrown together. I use to love watching wrestling and see the storylines evolve and that would make people want to buy the PPV. Now a days they build the main event and thats about it. If a wrestler has a problem with anther wrestler they'll do an interview and of course say, i'll meet you at whatever ppv is next. This WrestleMaina also disappoints because the way it was packaged. The last three WrestleMaina's were neatly packed three discs sets with tons of bonus footage and the Hall of Fame ceremony in its complete form all for $20. These year they did a two disc set with zero bonus footage but made a speical "tin" WrestleMaina for about five dollars more with all the extra features. Jeez, losing money or what Vince?Jeff Hardy VS Matt Hardy VS Ken Kennedy VS Edge VS Randy Orton VS Finlay VS King Booker VS CM Punk in a Money in the Bank Ladder Match: The highlight of the last few WrestleMaina's and this was no expection. Putting Hardy and Punk in the match was a good idea. Too bad neither man won it. It did however suffer from too many wrestlers and some disappered for awhile. Good opener though.Great Khali VS Kane: Ive seen Khali live. I know Vince likes big men but come on. Im surprised Smackdown didnt go bankrupt with him as champion. He cannot wrestle at all and Kane really has nothing better to do anymore.Chris Benoit VS MVP: MVP improved this year because of his many matches with Benoit. This would be one of many they had in the coming months. A good match.Batista VS the Undertaker: Of course you knew who would win this match. It was a very exciting match between the two. Again, the first of many encounters between these two.The ECW Originals VS the New Breed: Alright ECW you've got five minutes. Show us what you dont have. They'd have a rematch two days later that was 100% better then this crapfest.Bobby Lashley vs. Umaga: I remember seeing Lashley when he first started out. Couldnt wrestle then and cant wrestle now. A high profile match but I really could careless who wins.Melina vs. Ashley Massaro: As my other WWE reviews say, I hate women wrestling.John Cena VS Shawn Michaels: Good match and I really hope to see Michaels win the world title before he retires. Cena again is put on top much to the hatered or love of his fans.A pretty poor event. Something was missing from the show but I cant really put my finger on it.

reviewText: Im back with a wrestlemania 23 review. so thanks for reading and please comment.Money in the bank ladder match-edge vs. jeff hardy vs. randy orton vs. booker t vs. cm punk vs. mr.kennedy vs matt hardy vs. finlayThis match is 19 min. of awesome. This was very fast paced through the whole match and is very enjoyable and has some Joey Styles Oh My God moments. This match is Highflying, exciting, and freckin brutal. I wasn't happy that mr.kennedy won because he was still a rising star here. Awesome moments when edge went through the ladder, punk getting rkoed off the ladder, booker t pulling out a mini ladder, and edge having a spear fest. A lot of moments that stole the show. But the stupidest thing is that Jeff Hardy wasted a perfect time to become the number 1 contender to the wwe or world title.match rating:8/10Kane vs. The great khaliThis was the stupidest match on the card. this match shouldn't have even been at wrestlemania, this wouldn't even be a main event match on smackdown. This match was lame and slow paced. Not a good match to watch and should have been the opener.match rating:1/10United states championship-chris benoit(C) vs. MVPThis match was okay. There is a lot of technical wrestling in this match by benoit. Suplexes, submissions, and some dirty work by mvp. I honestly think their match at backlash and judgment day is better and more physical. Another average match on the card with benoit pulling off the win to retain.match rating:6/10World Heavyweight championship-Batista(C) vs. UndertakerThis match is great. Way better than the mitb match. To me, this and the wwe title match is the matches of the night. To me, this match was definatly worth getting match of the year for 07. Great match with some great mania' moments like batista power slamming taker through the anounce table, the dive over the top rope, the batista bomb, and the winning tombstone. stupid that this wasn't the main event because taker' won the rumble, but this match stole the show.match rating:10/10ECW originals(tommy dreamer, rvd, sandman, sabu) vs. new breed(Marcus Cor Von, Elijah Burke, Matt Striker, Kevin Thorn)This match was also okay. But had some extreme moments with sabu and rvd. The originals pulled off almost a big win. Also, ECW originals earning a spot for ecw in the wwe. This match isn't as good as their extreme rules match on ecw.match rating:7/10Battle of the billionares(hair vs hair match)-Umaga vs. bobby lashely(special guest ref. stone cold steve austin)This a good match here. Impressive action between two big guys like bobby lashely and umaga. Funny moment when mr.mcmahon got attacked by trump. Great moments when shane did a coast to coast, a stunner and spear on umaga, mr.mcmahon getting a michael jordon shave, and trump getting stunned. This match was what headlined wrestlemania, but was mostly hype. These two had a good rivalry going and had a solid match with some brawling from trump and mcmahon. Funny moment at the end when stone cold stunned trump.Match rating:7.5/10womens championship-Melina vs. AshleyThis match didn't deserve to be the match before the main event. This match, like all the other diva matches, stunk to.Match rating:2/10WWE championship-John Cena(C) vs. Shawn MichaelsGreat match here. Also, standing ovations for both men. HBK had the biggest pop, but cena had the best entrance crashing a brand new mustang through the mania' glass. This was a regular, yet extreme match. Extreme moments with a moonsault on the announce table and a piledriver on the steps. a coward moment when michaels slaped cena at the begining. But cena pulling off another impressive win over HBK with the stf. This match is really fast paced and is great, but didn't deserve to be mania's main event.match rating:9/10Overall, a great event here. This is my second favorite wrestlemania 20 years after wm 3 in detroit. This dvd is mostly worth getting for the money in the bank, world title, and wwe title matches.
summary: cena, taker, and a great event

reviewText: Match #1: Money in the Bank Ladder Match-- A total spot-fest as could probably be expected. Tons of high spots, although the match seemed a little TOO partitioned off throughout most of it. It went from big spot set up to big spot set up. They would probably benefit by cutting a few guys out of the match next year. This was a fun train wreck sort of match. ***Match #2: The Great Khali v. Kane-- There's a cardinal rule in wrestling that if you suck, suck to the point where you're suck-age is awesome. Khali is the sort of guy that fits that bill. He's a great attraction, throw away sort of act that we can all have fun with, but not expect a lot out of. Kane on the other hand, hasn't had decent stuff in forever. In fact, i'd argue that Kane hasn't been all that strong since at least 2001, as he was one of the very few bright spots during the invasion angle. As you can surmise, this one is pretty awful, but surprisingly watchable, as they keep it interesting enough with well-placed big man high spots including a nasty bump to the floor on the part of Khali, and a pretty cool looking body slam from Kane. All in all harmless, but not anywhere near good. *1/2Match #3-- United States Championship: Chris Benoit v. M.V.P.-- The crowd were really getting into it at exactly the point they ended it. This was sensational for what we got, but seemed like it was missing an entire third of the match. No problems with the headbutt finish (in fact it's nice to see a finisher actually, you know, finish a match) as much as it just sort of happened and that was it. Very similar to JBL-Cena at WM 21 where we basically had the heel controlling the action, one comeback spot and then the finish out of the blue. This would be fine if it was on any other show other than Wrestlemania. **1/2 because it didn't really take off. This was on track for around ***1/2.Match #4: World Heavyweight Championship: Batista v. The Undertaker-- It's a crime this was as far down the card as it ended up being. A lot of the reason for that was the total loss of heat on Batista's part from December all the way through now. This match, strangely enough, will change that. This is easily the best match of Batista's career and probably one of the best Undertaker WM matches, if not THE best. This is absolutely sensational. Unlike the main event, which is a marathon, this is a sprint. There isn't a dead moment of time and the entire time you've got great action. These two basically point Bazookas at each other and just fire away. Of course, that's not wise to do if you're facing the Dead man. Just a great, great story told. Sure, it's 15 minutes but really, the way this match plays out, it's a perfect amount of time considering what they were going for. This is an excellent, excellent match. ****Match #5: ECW Originals v. The New Breed-- Whew, total train wreck. Their match the following Tuesday on ECW on Sci Fi was MUCH, MUCH better than this. This would have barely passed for an average TV match. This was pretty much a train wreck. *Match #6: Battle of the Billionaires: Bobby Lashley (w/ Trump) v. Umaga (w/ Vince McMahon & Armando Alejandro Estrada)-- If you like Sports Entertainment then you're going to love the debacle that is this match. There's a Shane-O-Mac run in, a few stunners, beer drinking, a head shaving, a celebrity beat-down.. Umaga is a outstanding worker and brings a lot to the table in terms of energy and really helps things along in the  ring with a pretty green Lashley. This is a decent enough match but it's really more about the spectacle surrounding the match. I know there are a ton of people who love to break down the arm bars and whatnot, but I prefer to rate matches on what the story being told in the ring is. If they execute what they're going for well, then it gets praise. This is totally nuts and there's absolutely nothing wrong with it. It's a ton of fun and high energy. The folks that tuned in for this match certainly got their money's worth. ***Match #7: WWE Women's Championship: Melina v. Ashley-- Holy smokes this was bad. There was just no assemblence of anything, even the lumber jills on the outside of the ring. These two basically seemed to be buying time to cool the crowd down for the main event. DUDMatch #8: WWE Championship: John Cena v. Shawn Michaels-- This was sensational. I know many of the ADD fans these days don't understand the concept of building a match, and also think every move has to go somewhere or do something. If you're one of those folks, it's understandable why you don't like this match. Unlike Batista-Taker earlier in the night, this is a marathon and the story progresses at a far slower pace. Both of these guys, by style, are counter punchers. Both usually wrestle matches where they get beat up and come back. This is certainly a departure of that usual structure for both, and it made for some fun stuff. Michaels completely out wrestles Cena in the beginning but Cena hangs around long enough for HBK to make a mistake. When HBK gets busted open, he's now got to ditch the game plan and go to striking with Cena, who's nearly unbeatable in that kind of match. It quickly goes down hill for HBK from there and he eventually gets caught up in a SENSATIONAL final 7-10 minutes where the near falls really make for some great drama. Before I get into a rating I just want to comment on the leg work everyone gets all crappy-face for. The leg work was used in the context that HBK was only working it to maintain control. He wasn't looking to use it later on and never did. Cena's no selling of it wasn't much different from Kawada's no selling Misawa's leg work in what many consider the greatest match ever in 94... This is similar. This is a great story and has some outstanding drama. Probably the match of the night ****1/4This is a great Wrestlemania in that all four big-attraction matches really deliver. The stuff that you'd expect to suck, did, but the stuff that we expected to be good was in fact, great. To be honest, I really can't remember the time I legitimately dolled out two **** ratings on a WWE card. This was a legitimately fun Wrestlemania with a real great 'big time' feel that's sorely been lacking in the past few editions. This is easily the best Mania since XIX and may in fact be better. I've ordered my copy, you should order yours.

reviewText: (Money in the Bank Ladder Match)Edge vs Randy Orton vs CM Punk vs Finlay vs Jeff Hardy vs Mr Kennedy vs Matt Hardy vs King Booker: Wow those names took up a lot of review space, so I'll make it short and sweet. 8 men. Money in the Bank. All hell breaks loose. Not as good as 21's. Better than 22's. Now that's what I call a summarization. 9/10Kane vs The Great Khali: Giant vs Giant, great match right? Ha! On the other hand, if this match had been hardcore or in a steel cage...now that'd be a different story. That'd be...Wrestlemania!!! But unfortunately it isn't. It wasn't. Any questions? 4/10(United States Championship)Chris Benoit vs MVP: MVP? M-V-P? MMMMMMMVVVVVVPPPPPP?.......Nope, no matter how you say it, that word just doesn't belong at Wrestlemania. Regardless of how bad the idea was, a good performance by MVP. He really stepped up at Wrestlemania. Perhaps he has a future as a main eventer (ha!). Seriously, see this instead of going to the bathroom. It's pretty good. After the last match, anything looks good. 7.5/10(World Heavyweight Championship)Batista vs Undertaker: Many were unhappy about this not being the main event. But c'mon, Raw always gets the main event. ALWAYS. But I'm actually rather happy this was mid card. It added balance to the placement of the matches and kept the crowd on their toes. Slower and shorter than it could've been, but hey how can you complain in a match with Undertaker? You can't. End of story. 8.5/10ECW Originals vs The New Breed: I was really looking forward to this match but then. I asked myself....No Hardcore? No eliminations? No stipulations whatsoever? No excitement from the crowd? No high flying moves? No suspense? No longer than 5 minutes?......... NOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!!!!! 5.5/10(Hair vs Hair Match)Mr McMahon vs Donald Trump: 2 billionaires go at it. The loser gets his head shaved. Hm.Too much publicity for this match gave you an extremely empty feeling at the end, but this match still hides the fact that most of the other matches stink. They sure got us. Hooray for shifty marketing schemes!!!! 8/10(Women's Championship Lumberjill Match)Melina vs Ashley: This match has nothing, or does it? At least Ashley would make a better champi......Well, at least they added the lumberjills to t... Well, at least it was only 3 minu.....This match has nothing. 2/10(WWE Championship)John Cena vs Shawn Michaels: This was great. A great bout between 2 great competitors. They both put their heart and soul into it, something rarely seen in most matches today. Honestly, the right man won. Best main event of the past 3 Wrestlemanias. 9.5/10Overall: Too much hype went into this Wrestlemania. The fact that it was being held in Detriot (same spot as Wrestlemania 3) automatically meant it had to be the most spectacular Wrestlemania of all time. Yeah right. This was plain and simply, a good PPV. Nothing more, nothing less. Sure they could've made a tag team match(Brian and Paul)as well as other matches with different combinations of superstars. But they put on a great show and worked with what they had. It was a great, but not spectacular. What can I say? It's WRESTLEMANIA!!!!!!! 8.5/10

reviewText: This WrestleMania turned out to be the biggest event in the history of the company with it being completely centered around the fact that they return to Detroit 20 years after the historic WrestleMania 3...hense the nickname of "All Grown Up."  Thoughout the night, you'll see WWE revisit & try to recreate classic moments from that event such as Aretha Franklin returning to WrestleMania to sing the National Anthem once again.  And one thing to really check out was all the different & unique entrances."Money In The Bank" Ladder Match - Edge vs. Randy Orton vs. King Booker vs. Finlay vs. Matt Hardy vs. Jeff Hardy vs. CM Punk vs. Mr. Kennedy...Kennedy (sorry, I had to do that) - Damn, they knew how to kick this PPV off in style and this was the best Money In The Bank match to date.  Not every participant was able to get a "highlight reel" spot but everyone held their own & was able make this the one of the best matches of the night.  Some great moments to look out for where Edge's elimination from the match thanks to Jeff Hardy, Randy Orton recieving the Bookend off the ladder, and even Finlay's Hornswaggle getting in on some of the action...plus the return of the spinarooni!!!!Kane vs. Great Khali - I guess the appeal here was two giants fighting each other but past that & WWE trying to recreate the "Hogan slamming Andre" moment, this was a poor match.United States Champion Chris Benoit vs. MVP - This match got the least amount of hype than any other match on the card...to the point where Benoit didn't even appear on the final edition of SmackDown before the PPV.  We all know the quality Benoit can bring to a match but the shock was how much MVP was able to hold his own in the ring & display some technical wrestling of his own.  This was the "sleeper" match of the night.World Champion Batista vs. Undertaker - Taker's Undefeated Streak vs. Batista's Title and I'll be point blank honest, this was the match that should have ended the show.  This was Batista's best showing since he returned from his injury as he stepped up his game & didn't show any lack of effort like most of his previous performances.  This was a classic "big money" WrestleMania match & the match of the night for me as you saw the crowd off the chain thoughout the bout & even moments where it looked like Batista was going to end the streak & one spot to look out for would be Undertaker's big dive onto Batista.  It's ironic that this was the 20 year anniversary of WrestleMania 3 but Undertaker walks out of his WM the same way he did 10 years earlier...as a champion.ECW Originals vs. New Breed: Rob Van Dam, Tommy Dreamer, Sandman, Sabu vs. Marcus Cor Von, Elijah Burke, Matt Striker, Kevin Thorn - This match was actually the biggest shock of the night because the ECW originals won which alot of people didn't expect.  This match wasn't long enough for everyone to standout but it was good for what it was.  If you happen to get the Blockbuster Video exclusive version of this DVD set, you'll see their Extreme Rules rematch.  For those trivia fans, this was the WM debut for everyone in this match except RVD."Battle Of The Billionaries" Hair vs. Hair Match with special referee Stone Cold Steve Austin - Umaga w/Vince McMahon vs. Lashley w/Donald Trump - If you eliminate all the hype featuring McMahon/Trump...this was just an average match as Lashley & Umaga didn't really do anything  here outside of their normal routine to the point where the match got dull at times & Shane McMahon's "Coast 2 Coast" was the most impressive move in the bout.  The eventual ending happened with Umaga getting a stunner & spear before Mr. McMahon got a "Mr. Clean" haircut...and Donald Trump got a stunner.Womens Champion Melina vs. Ashley - Instead of following the formula done at WM20 & 22 where the Playboy diva was put into a seperate attraction match, this was a repeat of WM21 where the girl gets a Womens title match only because she got naked in the magazine.  Melina tried her best to carry Ashley but she just wasn't any good as the best move she did in the match was an elbow drop from the second rope.  Looking at all the divas at ringside & the catfight afterwards couldn't have saved this match.WWE Champion John Cena vs. Shawn Michaels - Cena's entrance for this WM heavily makes up for this "Chicago mobsters" entrance from last year...and for those who saw the PPV live, the streaker has been edited out of the DVD release.  As I said earlier, this match should have switched places with the Taker/Batista match as it would have been an outstanding undercard match but it wasn't a match that was worthy of being the main event.  HBK showed some good storytelling by working on Cena's leg thoughout the bout but unfortunally, Cena gave the performance that anti-Cena marks use when labeling him "superman" in that he no-sold his hurt leg  at times & along with the piledriver on the steps he got earlier.  This match was very much like his main event match with Triple H which means that it was a great match for what it was but it wasn't the quality that people would expect from a WrestleMania main event.Now there are three different versions of this DVD (why?  I don't know!).  One version is just the event itself (which is the one that I saw) while the other is loaded with other extras such as highlights from the WM press conference, the preshow lumberjack match with Ric Flair & Carlito vs. Gregory Helms & Chavo Guerrero, and the Hall Of Fame ceremony honoring Mr. Perfect, Jim Ross, Jerry Lawler, Dusty Rhodes, Mr. Fuji, Wild Samoans, Nick Bockwinkle, and The Original Sheik.  The third version is the Blockbuster exclusive that includes bonus extras such as the contract signing for the Battle Of The Billionaries match along with the Extreme Rules match between the ECW originals vs. New Breed from ECW on Sci-Fi.Overall, this was an good WrestleMania as the only matches that were poor were the Womens match along with the Kane/Khali match.  However I would recommend the Ultimate Edition along with the Hall Of Fame to get the most bang for your buck...unless you can get your hands on the Blockbuster version.  I recommend but try to get the most bang for your buck & get one of the other two versions instead of just the event only edition.
summary: 20 Years Later, They Return To Detroit...All Grown Up

reviewText: 1) Money in the Bank-Really good match with Kennedy, Punk, Booker Finlay, Edge, Orton and the Hardys. Despite a lot of predictions for this one and a couple of favorites standing out Kennedy pulled out the win. Kennedy's win was well deserved though I would have liked to see Edge or Orton win it. Kenney though has jobbed plenty of matches recently to Batista and Lashley it was only time before he won a big match.2) Khali vs. Kane-Ugh....the battle of one monster vs. a horrible wrestler and monster. Thankfully this match didn't last too long.3) US Title Match Benoit vs. MVP-Easy to call Benoit won. No way he was going to lose in Wrestlemania. A good match.4) The Undertaker vs. Batista for the World Title- Yes!!!! After five years the Undertaker was going to get his title again. He put over so many guys in the last five years from Brock Lesnar, John Cena, Kennedy and the dreaded John Heidenrich and JBL who are no longer wrestling. Despite what others said that it would be awful it was good. Undertaker carried Batista to a match and did his routine. He even did his big suicide dive of the ropes to the outside. Batista and Taker battled inside and outside. Batista went for a powerbomb but Taker countered and won the World Heavyweight Title!!!! Undertaker goes 15-0 at Mania.5) ECW Originals vs. The New Breed- Match didn't last long but Originals (Dreamer, Sabu, RVD and others) won it.6) Lashley vs. Umaga with Trump and McMahon in their corners, the "Battle of the Billionares" in a hair vs. hair match with Stone Cold as the special referee- Surprisingly watchable. Lashley took out Estrada and Lashley early on. Shane and Vince tried to screw Lashley but Stone Cold intervened and Lashley won. We get to see McMahon shaved bald by Donald Trump himself!!!!7) Lumberjill match for the Women's title Ashley vs. Melina- Crap match that should have been at the beginning not near the end. Thankfully this match was short.8) Shawn Michaels vs. John Cena for the WWE Title!!!Shawn Michaels is Wrestlemania!!!! Whether you like him or don't you know he's going to put a great match no matter who his with.HBK-Started chopping Cena and started working on his arm. Cena and HBK go of the ropes and Cena catches him with a clothesline Cena catches HBK with a shoulder block but Hbk catches with a press and punches him HBK gives Cena ahiptoss to the outside. HBK does a springboard to Cena on the announcers table!!!!!!!! HBK chops Cena on the outside and inside. Hbk works on Cena's leg and hits it on the post!!!A great hard fought match with Cena and HBK. Cena's improved but you know with HBK this match was going to be a classic.. They both gave it their all with another impressive performance (as expected) by HBK. Unfortunately Cena retained.All in all still a decent Wrestlemania.

reviewText: I'll always enjoy Wrestlemania because this is the event where moments become legendary and dream matches happen. 2007 was my final year in high school and this was a great Wrestlemania to see. It may be a bit smaller than the Manias before this one, but I still think the card was fine.Money In The Bank Ladder Match - Edge vs. Randy Orton vs. King Booker vs. Finlay vs. Matt Hardy vs. Jeff Hardy vs. CM Punk vs. Mr. Kennedy- First let me say, why was Edge & Randy Orton in this match? Don't get me wrong, I love both wrestlers but I wished they had a one on one match on this PPV instead. Anyway, if you've seen the last MITB matches; then you know what to expect with this match. It was a great opener to start the show. Everyone put on a fine performance. The main highlight is when Jeff Hardy dives on Edge on ladder outside the ring, which results in breaking the ladder (and Edge for that matter) in half. The winner comes as a complete shock to me.8/10Kane vs. Great Khali- Apart from Kane's tribute to Hulk Hogan slamming Andre The Giant 20 years ago, this match was really bad. Khali looks like a tree getting torn down everytime he wrestles. Kane deserves better!2/10United States Champion Chris Benoit vs. MVP- This was Benoit's final Wrestlemania before his tragic event. I must say, this was an entertaining match. Any of Benoit's matches were fantasic to just great and this was no different. MVP showed some skills here too. It's not the best match of the night, but don't skip either.7/10World Heavyweight Champion Batista vs. Undertaker- This was Taker's first title shot at Mania since 1997. Like everyone says, I think this should have been the main event. I mean Taker won the Royal Rumble and this two men have never fought against each other before. So why wasn't it? Anyway, I gonna say that this was my favorite match of the night!! It was so unpredictible and fast paced. There were many great moments like Taker diving over the top rope to Batista slamming Taker into the tables. The crowd was really into it as well. This was the match I wanted to see the most and it suprassed my expectations!10/10ECW Originals: Rob Van Dam, Tommy Dreamer, Sandman, Sabu vs. New Breed: Marcus Cor Von, Elijah Burke, Matt Striker, Kevin Thorn- This was a match I really didn't care much for. It was entertaining, but I didn't care at all for ECW. This match though was great to show off some new talent like The New Breed. But overall, it's a forgetable match. RVD should have been in MITB!5/10Battle Of The Billionaries" Hair vs. Hair Match - IC Champ Umaga w/Vince McMahon vs. ECW Champ Bobby Lashley w/Donald Trump with special referee Stone Cold Steve Austin- This was the most hyped up match of the event. Honestly, this match was nothing speical. Austin didn't really add to the match and it was a predictible fight. This could have been an typical match on RAW. The aftermath it funny though with Vinny Mac getting his head shaved bald and Trump getting stunned my Stone Cold (which looks really bad). Not a great match, but not as bad as everyone makes it out to be.6/10Womens Champion Melina vs. Ashley- Oh god, what is up with WWE placing really bad Diva matches before the main event? They did this the year before as well. As for the match, just skip because it's like every other Diva match.1/10WWE Champion John Cena vs. Shawn Michaels- I will admit, this was a better match than I expected; but it still was  a pretty predicible match. Still, this was the 2nd best match of the night next to WHC title match eariler. Micheals is always great in any match he's in and Cena CAN put on a good show (sorry Cena haters). Both men put on a good show. Watch for Cena getting piledriven onto the steel steps. It's a no brainer to realize Cena was gonna win because Micheals had no interest in winning another title. Still, I enjoyed this match and Cena's car enterance. But I still think Taker & Batista's match would have been a better closer for the event.9/10Overall, I really enjoyed this Wrestlmaina despite it having smaller card than the previous Manias before. I was glad to have watched this was gonna to be the last Wrestlemania I'd see as a high schooler. The next manias I'd see as the next phase of my life would begin- Collage! My personal favorite match of the night was Taker vs. Batista and it was the one everyone was talking about the next day at school. It also began a great year long feud between the two. Don't pass this Mania up, it's great!
summary: The last Wrestlemania I saw in high school.

reviewText: 1. MITB- Great match as it was expected. You really can't fail with this match and this match was tied for motn. Great spot with hardy's legdrop onto edge. Awesome match! 9.5/102. Still worth watching. 9.5/10

reviewText: 20 years ago Wrestlemania invaded the city of Detroit, headlined by Andre The Giant vs. Hulk Hogan and now 20 years later in the same city we have Wrestlemania 23.Disc 1-Aretha Franklin sings "America The Beautiful", a good rendition to say the least.-Money In The Bank Ladder Match, Jeff Hardy vs. Finlay vs. Mr. Kennedy vs. Matt Hardy vs. King Booker vs. Randy Orton vs. CM Punk vs. Edge: This was the usual spot fest though Finlay hit a nice splash from the top rope onto the outside. Matt and Jeff do team up despite this being every man for themselves, but they do take it to each other at the top of a ladder. Jeff hits a huge splash off of a ladder onto the outside slamming Edge through another ladder. Orton hits a massive RKO off the ladder on Punk then Booker hits a Book End on Orton soon after. Hornswoggle makes an appearance but gets knocked off the ladder by Kennedy and shortly after Kennedy hits Punk with a ladder and climbs up to get the briefcase, Kennedy wins. 8/10.-The Great Khali vs. Kane: The bookers for this show must've said, that first match was great, but we need to slow things down a lot and so comes this match. Its the usual big man vs. big man match, but its not very good, not that Kane didn't try but Khali is so immobile he makes it so hard for anyone to have a good match with him. Kane does take Khali off his feet at one point and even executes an impressive slam on the 420lb monster after giving him a low blow thanks to a chain and hook. Khali hits his chokeslam and covers Kane with one foot to win. 4/10. Afterwards Khali chokes Kane out with the chain.-Funny thing backstage with Cryme Time trying to cheer up Eugene bringing in Extreme Expose. Mae Young and Moolah make an appearance along with numerous stars from the past, like Slick, Dusty Rhodes, Sgt. Slaughter, I.R.S., Ricky Steamboat, Jimmy Hart and of course Ron Simmons ending it as only he can.-United States Championship Match, Chris Benoit (Champion) vs. MVP: Now this was a good back and forth contest, as MVP held his own in his first Wrestlemania against the veteran Chris Benoit. MVP was able to counter a lot of Benoit's offense including locking on his own type of submissions. MVP is also able to stay a step ahead of Benoit for a good portion of the match. Its probably one of the best technical wrestling matches at a Wrestlemania in quite some time. Benoit ends up hitting the diving headbutt and makes the cover to retain his title. 8/10. Side Note: Sort of eerie looking back now, hearing how the annoucers talked up Benoit and how the crowd cheered for him especially with what would happen just 3 months later.-Hall of fame highlights are shown of the inductees then they are brought out to the live audience. The list includes Jerry "The King" Lawler, Jim Ross, Mr. Fuji, The Wild Samoans, Nick Bockwinkel, Mr. Perfect (accepted by his family), The Original Sheik (accepted by his wife) and Dusty Rhodes.-World Heavyweight Championship Match: Batista (Champion) vs. The Undertaker: Wow how this wasn't higher on the PPV card I'll never know, they worked so well together countering each others moves on several occasions. These two delivered big time in a match where the animal gave it his all to end the streak but in the end Taker hits the Tombstone to become the World Champion. There aren't enough words to describe this match, watch it an enjoy. 10/10.-Eight Man Tag Team Match, The Sandman, Tommy Dreamer, RVD and Sabu vs. Elijah Burke, Matt Striker, Marcus Cor Von & Kevin Thorn: Its the ECW Originals vs The New Breed and its not a bad match but it should've been a hardcore rules match as putting guys like Sabu & The Sandman in a regular match makes their flaws more obvious. Each guy gets a chance to get his spots in and for a time the New Breed dominates. RVD ends up hitting the frog splash on Striker and pins him and the Originals win the match. 6/10.-Battle of the Billionaires, Hair vs. Hair Match, Umaga (Representing Vince McMahon) vs. Bobby Lashley (Representing Donald Trump) w/Special Referee Stone Cold Steve Austin: Quite a bit of build-up to this one and its fairly pedestrian for being this high up on the card. Both Lashley and Umaga are a lot alike style wise so you get a lot of power moves and also the expected involvement of Vince's son Shane, even attempting the Coast to Coast on Lashley and hitting it. Austin of course gets involved stunning a couple of people including Umaga and Lashley hits the spear to pin Umaga. 6/10. The aftermath of Vince getting his head shaved his quite funny to say the least. Also nice to see Trump get stunned.-Lumberjill Match for the WWE Women's Championship, Ashley vs. Melina (Champion): Its the usual divas match where its used to cool down the audience from the previous match and its really not that good. Not that both didn't try but Ashley never had any business in the ring. The Lumberjills do play a part in the match throwing the women back in when they are outside the ring. Melina ends up reversing a rollup to pin Ashley and retain her title. 4/10. There's the expected mini-brawl with all the women which gets a bigger reaction than the match itself.Disc 2-WWE Championship Match, John Cena (Champion) vs. Shawn Michaels: Probably Cena's best wrestling match at a Wrestlemania, Michaels makes him look great and also it was nice to see Shawn be the main event again and he did steal the show. Plenty of good counter wrestling, the expected high spots from Michaels and of course Cena's usual offense. Cena does end up locking on the STFU and after battling to get out of it Michaels finally taps out. Great main event, 10/10.Extras-Commercials that hype the main matches-All Grown Up Vignettes with the Superstars.-Highlights of the Wrestlemania 23 Press Conference-Stone Cold Steve Austin Announce As The Special Guest Referee: Very good segment from Raw that had the crowd chanting for Austin before he even came out.-No Way Out Rematch, Raw 3/26/07: John Cena & Shawn Michaels vs. The Undertaker & Batista: A good tag team match with both the Wrestlemania main event players teaming up. God way to build up on the final Raw before Wrestlemania.-WWE.com interview: Maria interviews CM Punk before Wrestlemania 23Disc 3The Entire Hall of Fame Ceremony: The best speeches are by Jim Ross, Curt Henning (done by his family, very emotional) and Dusty Rhodes.Other inductees include: Nick Bockwinkel, Mr. Fuji, The Wild Samoans, The Original Sheik and Jerry "The King" Lawler.For being the 20 year return to Detroit, there were a couple of duds but the main event and even the U.S. title matches were well worth watching.
summary: 20 years later but comes up a little short of great

reviewText: The 8 way Money In The Bank ladder match was a high-flying,hard-hitting showstealer. The match between The Great Khali & Kane was slow & sloppy. The Chris Beniot-MVP-US title match was a high-tech,solid bout. The World's title match between The Undertaker & Batista was a hard-hitting,smash-mouth brawl. The 8 man tag team match between The ECW Originals & The New Breed was short but sweet. The Bobby Lashley-Umaga match was not great but pretty good with VKM & Donald Trump making the match at least entertaining. The Melina-Ashley-Lumberjill match for the Women's title was short,sloppy and dumb. The HBK-John Cena-WWE title match was a back-and-forth,entertaining,hard-hitting,high-flying bout. I give this PPV a 8 out of 10.

reviewText: 80-76%-perfect75-71%-awsome70-66%-good65-61%-poor60-56%-awful1. The money in the bank ladder match- Now this is what you call a great way to kick off the show. This I would say is a step up from last years ladder match but a step down from the first one. There was some good action to kick off the show that included some sick ladder shots that busted people wide open. There was one spot in the match that was amazing when Jeff set Edge on a ladder and Jeff climbed to the top of the ladder inside the ring and jumped off it which sent edge crashing through the ladder and broke it in half. Another nice spot were randy orton hit an RKO on Finlay from the top of the ladder. One more sick spot was when Little Bastard was set on Mr. Kennedy's shoulders and jumped off the ladder and sent him crashing to the canvas below. Just an awesome match to kick off the show. Winner Mr. Kennedy. Match Rating 9/10.2. Kane vs. The Great Kalhi- Now this is what we thought it would be and that is a crap fest. Some people say Kane has lost his touch but I just think this was because of his opponent who cant wrestle. This was a lot of chops and boots. The one spot in the match that Kane picked up Kalhi and scooped slammed him down but that's about it. Winner The Great Kalhi. Match Rating 3/10.3.  Chris Beniot vs. MVP for the U.S. title- This was actually a solid match. Going into this match I was not to sure what you were going to see but this was just a solid wrestling match. MVP controlled a lot of this match but than beniot fought back and hit a head but off the top rope. Winner and still US Champ Chris Beniot. Match Rating 7/10.4. Batistia vs. Undertaker for the World Heavyweight Title- This was indeed a show stealer. Now I will say this was no steamboat savage like wrestlemania 3 but both guys stepped there game up here. There was some great action to start with a lot of outside ring action but than there was a classic undertaker spot were he jumped over the top rope on to batistia on the outside. There was also another nice spot were Batistia power slammed Taker through the table on the outside. Than there were a lot of near falls in a row were you were almost positive taker was going to win the title but Batistia kept on kicking out. Than batistia hit a batistia bomb on taker but taker kicked out again. After some back and forth action taker finished him off with a tombstone piledriver to close a great match by both men. Winner and new world heavy weight champ Undertaker. Match Rating 9/10.5. The ECW Originals vs. The New Breed- This was not the show stealer I was hoping for. This was not terrible but this was not given the time it was needed and they had plenty of it considering the show ended a half hour early. Also the sad thing was the next week they did the same match on TV and it was a hardcore match that was ten times better than this. To short and just passable. Winner The Ecw Originals. Match Rating 5/10.6. Bobby Lashley with Donald Trump vs. Umaga with Vince McMahon loser gets there head shaved- This was actually not that bad of a match. This for me was more of the entertainment factor than it was the wrestling factor. A lot of this match had Umaga control it but bobby fought back. When he tried to fight back shane mcmahon came down and went coast to coast and drive a trash can into bobby's face. After Austin came back in he cleaned house and lashey hit a spear for the win. After the match vince got his head shaved and he ended up leaving Donald with a stunner. Winner Bobby Lashley. Match Rating 7.5/10.7. Melina vs. Ashley for the wwe womens title- This was a filler to slow the crowd down after that match. This was just terrible there was nothing fun about this match. It was about 5 minutes long which was the right amount  of time. Melina got the win which was the only good thing about this. Winner and still wwe womens champ Melina. Match Rating 3/10.8. John Cena vs. Shawn Michales for the wwe title- This was another great match. I was not expecting this to be a bad match so it was no surprise it was good. It started out a little slow but than Michales hit a moon Sault off the ropes to the outside. After that there was just a lot of solid wrestling including Michales getting busted wide open. The last 6 minutes of this match was amazing as there were so many near falls and reversals but cena ended getting the win again by tap out which sucked. Winner and still wwe champ John Cena. Match Rating 9/10.Well that raps up another. I would give Wrestlemania 23 a grade of 52.5/80 which is a 66% which means this is a good ppv. People will look at this rating and be shocked well don't let this rating fool you. There were just to terrible match and a barley passable that made the grade so low. If you look at every thing else you have to great title matches and a great ladder match also the lashey match and beniot was still solid so I do recommend for you to pick this dvd up. If u can tell me if my review was helpful or not I would appreciate that thanks for your time.

reviewText: wrestlemania 23 was a good wrestlemania however it only had one match stole the show.match 1. 8 man money in the bank matchthis was the best money in the bank match yet. alot of sick moves and alot of blood. jeff hardy creates another wrestlemania moment and cm punk shows that he can  wrestle with the stars of the wwe. this match had alot of comedy in it as well for example the kennedy hornswoggle incident. the ending did not dissapoint either and overall it was a good match. 4/5match 2. great kahli vs kanethis was a horrible filler and a huge waste of time. The match was really slow and didn't start to pick up till about 20 minutes in. the last 10 minutes make the match. thier must've been 10 straight reverses and alot of kickouts. the people were on their feet when john had shawn in the stfu and they were screaming. the ending really hurt the match because the wrong man won.3.5/5wrestlemania had one match I could watch over and over again and a few matches that did not deserve to be here all in all good wrestlemania.8/10

reviewText: Wrestlemania 23 was a fun Wrestlemania, but not a great one. It is certainly the best Wrestlemania since Wrestlemania 20. But it was too short and featured two lousy matches.Jeff Hardy vs. Matt Hardy vs. Ken Kennedy vs. Edge vs. Randy Orton vs. Finlay vs King Booker vs. CM Punk in a Money in the Bank Ladder MatchLike all the other Money in the Bank Ladder Matches, this one was really good, and probably the best match on the card. Unlike the previous two matches of its kind, this one had eight wrestlers and may have suffered for it. The match seemed a little too congested. Regardless, there were some really nice spots and a lot of action. The guys were given about 20 minutes and they made the most of it. A great way to start the event.Great Khali vs. KaneA pretty lousy match. Kane is a decent wrestler but he cannot carry a guy, especially not one as bad as Khali. Was only 5 minutes long, but that was way too much.United States Champion Chris Benoit vs. Montel Vontavius PorterBenoit carried MVP through this and it came off pretty well. The match was timed well and was fun to watch. Definitely a welcome sight after the lousy Khali match.World Heavyweight Champion Batista vs. the UndertakerI dont know why the World Heavyweight Title match, which should be the main event by rights because the Undertaker won the Royal Rumble and earned the right to be in the main event. But regardless, it was a fun match. It was by no means a great match. Batista is not much of a wrestler and the Undertaker cant really carry people anymore. But the Undertaker always comes up big at Wrestlemania, and this match was very, very exciting. Perhaps due to the nostalgia of seeing the Undertaker in a world title match at Wrestlemania. Definitely a lot fun to watch.The ECW Originals versus the New BreedThis match was pretty poor. There were a couple nice spots, mainly by Rob Van Dam and Elijah Burke, but it was way too short for much to happen. It was also fairly typical of a tag match. The heels have the advantage, beat on a face, who gets the hot tag. Then all hell breaks loose and everyone is in the ring, etc., etc. Definitely the weakest match on the card to this point. But it was fun to see Sabu and the Sandman at Wrestlemania, since it is unlikely they'll ever be there again.Bobby Lashley vs. Umaga in a Hair versus Hair MatchThis was a terrible wrestling match, but managed to be fun to watch, thanks to Steve Austin and Shane McMahon getting in there. Neither Umaga nor Lashley can wrestle, and there wasnt much of it. It was just a lot of violence. Watching Vince get his head shaved was fun too. Fun, but extremely predictable.Women's Champion Melina vs. Ashley Massaro in a Lumberjill MatchThis was an awful match. Melina is a decent wrestler, as far as the women go, but Ashley is very poor and looked completely lost out there. This was more about the eye candy of the Lumberjills than it was about wrestling. It was given the three minutes women's wrestling matches typically are given. But I'm glad it was short.WWE Champion John Cena versus Shawn MichaelsThe main event came off pretty well. And it was pretty unusual for a Cena match. Cena matches typically have him dominating the whole way through except when his opponent cheats. But the match was choreographed so that Michaels was in control for most of it. Michaels really put his heart into this one and managed to make Cena look pretty good too. Pretty exciting, especially the conclusion, though it was fairly predictable. Not the best main event in Wrestlemania history, but definitely better than last years main events.All in all this was a fun Wrestlemania. But it was flawed. Despite being a four hour event, there was less than two hours of wrestling. A couple of the matches were pretty bad, and a couple other ones featured very little wrestling. But the Benoit/MVP match was pretty good, the Money in the Bank Match was a lot of fun. The Batista/Undertaker match was good too, especially if you're an Undertaker fan. It was also fun to see Vince get his head shaved. Finally, the main event was pretty good.This does not rate with the best Wresltemania's. It was way too short and some of the matches were pretty bad. But it had a few really fun matches. Its worth buying if you typically buy Wrestlemania DVDs, but if you only buy the really great ones, dont get this one.
summary: A Fun Wrestlemania, but not a Great One

reviewText: Wrestlemania 23:1. Jeff Hardy vs Edge vs Mr Kennedy vs Matt Hardy vs Randy Orton  vs Cm Punk vs Finlay vs King Booker Money In The Bank Ladder Match: This is the perfect way to kick of wrestlemania, 2nd best money in the bank match with some breathtaking spots including, jeff putting edge through a ladder, and orton hits an RKO off the top of a ladder, such a good match, even hornswoggle got involved and got his butt kicked from kennedy, so glad with the outcome, great match ****1/42. Great Khali vs Kane: This was not good at all, but I wasnt expecting much, very slow, dragged on, I just hated it, ending was fine and this was nothing more than a filler *3. Chris Benoit(c)vs MVP U.S title: I didnt enjoy this match than everyone else, I like both wrestlers but the pace was slow and it seemed to drag on, this was benoits last match at wrestlemania and it definatley wasnt his best **1/24. Batista(c)vs The Undertaker WH Title, Streak vs Title: I thought that this match was great, a lot of good power moves, good table spot, and at the end it was very fast paced with some good counters, in the middle of the match taker does his signiture leap of faith onto batista, overall a great championship match, but this shouldnt of been the 4th match ****5. ECW Originals vs New Breed: I thought that this was a pretty good match, better than I expected it to be, dreamer hits a sick DDT onto striker and sabu almost botches a dive out of the ring, overall this could of been worse, the ending was pretty good **3/46. Bobby Lashley vs Umaga Spec Ref= Steve Austin, If Lashley loses then Donald Truump has to have his head shaved, If Umaga loses then Vince Mcmahon has to have his head shaved: This is a good match, some good storyline telling, like it when shane mcmahon hit the coast to coast on lashley, the match moved along smoothly, great ending with austin getting involved, and the aftermath was even better ***1/47. John Cena(c)vs Shawn Michaels WWE Title: This was one of the best main events of all time, an amazing match in every way, some great counters, theres a sick spot in the middle where cena gets piledrivered onto steel steps, match went on for 28 minutes so it was given a great amount of time, it was just such a fun match to watch and you didnt know who was going to win, personally I think the wrong man won but that doesnt hurt the match one bit ****1/2Match of the Night: Cena vs MichaelsWorst Match of Night: Khali vs KaneMoment of Night: SPOILER= Mcmahon gets a haircut!Overall PPV: 8.25/10This has a must see match, a fun opener and a great world title match, I reccomend this dvd!

reviewText: WWE Wrestlemania XXIIIApril 1, 2007Ford Field Detroit, MI1. Money in the Bank Ladder MatchEdge vs. Jeff Hardy vs. CM Punk vs. Matt Hardy vs. Mr. Kennedy vs. King Booker vs. Finlay vs. Randy OrtonGreat way to start off the show and great action in this match. Edge and Orton both pull off a lot of their finishers in this match and Orton does his RKO off the ladder!!! There was two more wrestlers in this match which I don't know why WWE did that and it kind of lower the match greatness but still like all the MITB ladder matches this was great. Jeff does an incredible leap off a 20 foot ladder onto Edge which both men gets put out of the match. Gotta watch. Possibably match of the night. 4.5/52. Kane vs. Great KhaliI knew from the beginning this wasn't gonna be a good match at all. This match should have been  No Holds Barred or a chain match cause Khali can't wrestle at all and Kane aint good enough to carry the match. Cool to see Kane body slam Khali but the ending sucked. Only watch the first time. 1.5/53. United States ChampionshipChris Benoit (C) vs. MVPIt was good to see a nice match after the Kane/Khali match. Benoit mostly carries this match but MVP does have potential to be a big time wrestler later on down the road. Good match to watch with some nice counters & back and forth action. 4.5/54. World Heavyweight ChampionshipBatista (C) vs. UndertakerI was looking foward to this match being the main event. Taker had a nice enterance and good match all around. The crowd was pretty much all into this match. A very good back and forth contest here. The table spot was good to see. Taker hits the tombstone and becomes 15-0 and the new WHC. 4.75/55. ECW Originals vs. The New BreedNot a great 8 man tag match maybe if they added an extreme rules elimination stipulation to it but still an OK match to watch but defiantely not WM material. some nice spots with RVD. Their extreme rules match from ECW a week later was way better then this match. 3.25/56. Hair vs. Hair MatchBooby Lashley w/ Donald Trump vs. Umaga w/ Mr. McMahonSpecial Referee: Stone Cold Steve AustinThis match reminded me of the Goldberg/Lesnar match at WM XX which Austin refereed that match too. Austin made this match watchable like he did that match. Shane comes out and does his coast to coast trash can in the corner thing. A few hard hitting moves but nothing special. It was funny to see Vince get shaved bald but pretty predictable match. Greater to see Austin Stun both Vince and Donald. 2.25/57. WWE Women's ChampionshipLumberjill Match- Melina (C) vs. AshleyNot a good womens match by any means. Melina is alright and Ashley just look good to some degree but not a wrestler at all. To me it seem the match was more about the divas outside the ring but very short and it wasa good thing too. 1.25/58. WWE ChampionshipJohn Cena (C) vs. Shawn MichaelsThis was actually a good main event. In my opinion this was one of Cena's best matches ever and probably b/c he was in there with the Show Stopper. HBK really puts it all out there in this one and he also makes Cena looks like he knows what he is doing in the ring. The end really gets you on the edge of your seat and HBK pulls out all the stops. Defiantely one of Cena's finer matches. 4.5/5This isn't the best WM but if you are looking to buy it for your WM collection or you want to see Taker become champ again then you should but other than its up to you but if I had to pay 50 dollars again to see it on PPV I wouldn't pay for it.
